      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-solver-error-criteria",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear Newton-Raphson solver convergence monitored with force residual norm < 1e-6 and displacement residual norm < 1e-6 at every load increment. Load step sensitivity study confirmed QoI independence from increment size beyond 200 steps. Iterative linear solver (PCG with incomplete Cholesky preconditioner) tolerance set to 1e-10; direct solver cross-check performed on representative sub-model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-use-error-criteria",
      "rationale": "Simulation execution governed by detailed Standard Operating Procedure (SOP-FEA-001 rev. 4). Independent analyst re-ran full simulation from geometry import through post-processing; QoI agreement within 0.2%. Boundary condition application, material assignment, and contact definition reviewed by senior engineer and documented in peer-review checklist. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-model-form-criteria",
      "rationale": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening, Ti-6Al-4V) justified by literature and coupon-level calibration data. Frictional contact (mu=0.3, Augmented Lagrange) validated against independent contact patch tests. Geometric nonlinearity (NLGEOM) enabled throughout. Model form assumptions documented and sensitivity of QoIs to constitutive parameter variation assessed via Sobol first-order and total-order indices; model form uncertainty bounded at ±3.1% on stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-model-inputs-criteria",
      "rationale": "All material properties (E=114 GPa, yield=880 MPa, UTS=950 MPa, hardening=2.8 GPa) sourced from certified tensile coupon tests on production-lot Ti-6Al-4V per ASTM E8. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of 11 production screws (dimensional uncertainty ±0.01 mm). Input uncertainty distributions (normal, log-normal as appropriate) propagated through Monte Carlo ensemble (N=10,000 samples). Full input uncertainty budget documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-test-samples-criteria",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All specimens drawn from same production lot; certificate of conformance and dimensional inspection records archived. Sample size justification provided via statistical power analysis (power=0.90, alpha=0.05) demonstrating adequate detection of 10% QoI difference. No outliers excluded without documented justification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-test-conditions-criteria",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 protocol followed at both laboratories. Test fixture geometry, load application rate (5 mm/min), and environmental conditions (23±2°C, 50±10% RH) documented and controlled. Cross-laboratory reproducibility confirmed: inter-lab coefficient of variation < 3.5% for all QoIs. Boundary condition fidelity between test and model verified through fixture stiffness characterization and independent load-cell calibration records."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
