    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors assessed at requiredLevel=5 and achievedLevel=5 for MRL-5 package. Quantitative validation metrics (E/uval) are below the 1.96 threshold for all three QoIs (stiffness: 0.82, yield force: 1.14, force at 40 mm: 1.31). All QoI percent differences are within the pre-established 10% acceptance bound. Full uncertainty quantification including Monte Carlo propagation (N=10,000), global Sobol sensitivity analysis, and Richardson-extrapolated discretization error assessment are documented and linked. Software QA, code verification, and use-error controls meet MRL-5 rigor requirements. Test sample provenance, cross-laboratory reproducibility, and input-equivalency traceability are fully documented. No unresolved weakeners, open issues, or scope gaps identified. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the stated COU.",
